Two people have died after a bus and car crashed in Giyani Limpopo this morning. Transport and Community Safety spokesperson Mike Maringa said the Giyani to Nsami road is temporarily closed following a fatal accident. He said preliminary investigations revealed speeding as a possible cause of the accident. Maringa said the driver of the bus was trying to overtake two cars in front of him. The bus collided with a car, lost control and veered off the road and overturned. Two people were certified dead on the scene and 17 others were rushed to Khensani Hospital. The deceased were passengers in the bus.